&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: Neonatal Transport Fellow&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contract: 12 months, Fixed Term Contract&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please apply via NHS Jobs&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to appoint two (2) Clinical Fellows, for a period of 12 months. The post(s) will offer experience in the delivery of Neonatal Transport as a member of the Peninsula Neonatal Transport Service (PNTS) based in Derriford Hospital. PNTS is the transport service covering the southern sector of the South West Operational Delivery Network (SWODN) in the UK&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will also support a team of specialist registrars to provide out of hours cover to the middle tier neonatology rota. EWTD compliant, full shift systems are in place with no cross cover required between paediatrics and neonatology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For more information or an informal discussion, please contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Secretary to Dr John Madar, NICU, Level 5, Derriford Hospital, PL6 8DH&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Phone: 01752 431575 e-mail : &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;john.madar@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
